"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT badges.UserId)\nFROM badges\nJOIN users ON badges.UserId = users.Id\nWHERE badges.Name = 'Supporter' AND users.Age BETWEEN 19 AND 65;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct users who have obtained the \"Supporter\" badge and are classified as adults (age between 19 and 65). It joins the `badges` and `users` tables using the foreign key relationship `badges.UserId = users.Id`."